cretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8875.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idol of the Fallen</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Greig's End</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - (or &quot;My Hell Trip&quot;)<br>
<br>
Spent ages there last night... mostly durring a cr gone bad.  The place is a death trap, and you should be very careful traveling through it.  As a rogue I decided to scout a bit for our group... every mob I came across was indiff, and I got very deep in the zone looking for a way out on the other side. since I was so deep and not seeing any sign of a zone I decided to go for a CoH... so I request it and POP right on my spot a large mob that could see me, breaks my hide and everything jumps me.  I'm thinking &quot;its cool Im gettin CoHed&quot;... problem is it turns out CoH doesn't work in the zone.  So I die DEEP in, they decide to fight up to me as I make my way back for a possible summon and they all but wipe out.<br>
<br>
Sneek/Invis isn't really worth using at all in this zone as things that see you can pop outa nowhere at anytime and in any spot. It's a badddd place, and just be careful exploring (necros and monks are good, we had niether)... I died twice and lost 1 complete rez cause of corpse timer... this is a first for me!<br>
<br>
One of the neat things about the place is you turn into various models in the zone when the cratures in there proc on you, like you may look like a drake to yourself but to others you could be a centipede or a dog or a whatever... oh ya did I mention it's creepy in there?  It's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> sorta</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> like a massive semi-outdoor befallen, but on acid! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uravenwingedangel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ravenwinged Angel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/8/01 5:32:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8875.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idol of the Fallen</span><hr size=1> Grieg's end does have a zone in in Scarlet Desert too.<br>
<br>
One neat thing I found in echo caverns, in the secrent entrance path that leads to Fungal Grove is the evil Shadowhaven outpost.<br>
<br>
Soon as you zone in, if you take a right down the hall there is a boulder at the hall, a trigger on the wall opens the wall.<br>
<br>
Inside is a cave with forts and tents in it.  The inhabitants included merchants, including the necro spell merchant, guild trainers for rogues/warriors/casters etc and even a banker.<br>
<br>
And being a dark elf, everything was warmly as opposed to dubious which I seem to be everyplace else in Shadowhaven(but not The Bazaar which is NOT on SH merchant faction and is indifferent to everyone) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umikar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mikar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/8/01 6:15:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8875.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idol of the Fallen</span><hr size=1> We did Griegs End with a single group (2xclr, war, rng, enc and magi). <br>
<br>
Cleared everything up to the 2 locked doors with no deaths but a few close calls - but no key/rogue so we couldnt get to see Grieg himself nor a Servitor of Luclin (both red and on track). Dont really need a rogue for the traps - just trigger and kill.<br>
<br>
We had an off hand shaman only item drop - +10% alchemy but is was nodrop and norent. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugnomgue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gnomgue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/9/01 2:36:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8875.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idol of the Fallen</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ssrae Temple</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Took a 60 warrior, 60 rogue, 60 enchanter, 60 cleric, 60 druid, 60 shaman here.  First couple mobs double'd for 270 or so.  Went in the right door, Hail a Shissar warlock, level 52 necro that casts 1100 point lifetaps!  Hi Shissar Arcanist, level 52 wizard that casts sunstrike (1800 point DD) and the very difficult to resist 1200 point solist's ice spear!  Go up the spiraling ring thing, pull a temple beserker or something like that, double 333.  Go in the middle door, clear the way mostly, go left, go thru locked door, clear about 10 mobs come to a room with 10 more mobs, kill them all, kill a named called disciple something or other, had about 3k hp (or less, died in about 30 seconds heh) and @#%$ hits, ALOT easier than normal mobs.  At this point our druid fell thru the floor by the fake wall in this area and we had to get his corpse and left.<br>
<br>
Loot:<br>
Star Ruby<br>
11/15 throwing items<br>
<br>
... that is all, in 6 hours, including killing a named mob 3 times.  <br>
<br>
HUGE zone, probably has like 7 floors or so and they're all full of difficult mobs on a 20 minute respawn timer.  Don't expect to get away with bringing one group here unless it's of a composition similiar to mine with basically all level 60s.  <br>
<br>
Low level mobs make it a @#%$ zone to exp in for the difficulty, lack of loot makes it a @#%$ zone to raid.<br>
<br>
One more note, mobs have a TINY, TINY assist range.  Pretty small aggro range too.. but the assist range was about that of a large rat... nonexistent.  <br>
<br>
Some of this stuff probably changed, like the small assist range and lack of items, but even in the somewhat buggy and unitemized state it was in, my group had a blast fighting here, was quite the challenge for a well oiled level 60 group.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulleauaric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lleauaric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/10/01 12:53:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8875.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Idol of the Fallen</span><hr size=1> Did the Deep pretty far in..  considering the amount of Mobs in there..<br>
